\q1
\v 19 Betapa besar perkenan-Mu,
\q2 yang Kau sediakan untuk pengikut-Mu yang setia!
\q1 Di depan mata telanjang setiap orang, Kau limpahkan pada mereka yang berlindung pada-Mu.
\v 20 Kau sembunyikan mereka bersama-Mu, di mana mereka aman dari serangan-serangan manusia;
\q2 Kau sembunyikan mereka dalam perlindungan, di mana mereka aman dari serangan-serangan fitnah.and protect them from people who plot \add to kill them\add*.
\q1 You hide them in safe places from their enemies [MTY] who accuse/insult them.
\b
\v 21 Praise Yahweh!
\q2 When my enemies surrounded the city \add in which I was living\add*,
\q2 he showed me wonderfully that he faithfully loves me.
\q1
\v 22 I was afraid, and I cried out, “I have been separated from Yahweh!”
\q2 but you heard me and answered my cry for help.
\b
\q1
\v 23 You people who belong to Yahweh, love him!
\q2 Those who are loyal to him, he protects,
\q2 but those who are very proud, he punishes them severely like they deserve to be punished.
\q1
\v 24 You who confidently expect Yahweh \add to do great things foryou\add*,
\q2 be strong, be courageous!